// .cursorrules for Personal Tech Portfolio using 11ty
// Author: Sven Malvik - German Tech Leader from Norway

// Project Context
- This is an 11ty-based portfolio website showcasing tech leadership, trance music, and AI work
- Focus on clean, modern design with dark/light theme support
- Main sections include blog, docs, and trance music showcase

// Site Structure
Current 11ty folder structure:
- src/
  - _data/          // Site metadata, navigation, personal info
  - _includes/      // Templates, partials, CSS, scripts
    - css/         // Component and global styles
    - partials/    // Header, footer, navigation components
    - scripts/     // JavaScript components
    - webc/        // Web components
  - assets/         // Static assets
    - css/         // Global CSS
    - fonts/       // Custom fonts
    - images/      // Site images
    - scripts/     // Site scripts
    - svg/         // SVG icons and graphics
  - common/         // Shared content (404, robots.txt, etc.)
  - docs/          // Documentation pages
  - pages/         // Main site pages
  - posts/         // Blog posts

// Coding Standards
- Modern JavaScript (ES6+) modules
- Nunjucks templating
- CSS custom properties for theming
- BEM methodology for CSS
- WebC for custom components

// Content Guidelines
- Blog posts in markdown with frontmatter
- Documentation with code examples
- SVG icons for platform links
- Responsive images using 11ty-img

// Writing style for blog posts
- Use the writing_style.md as a guide for the writing style of blog posts, pages, and other content.

// Build Process
- Development: npm run start (live reload)
- Production: npm run build
- Favicon generation
- Asset optimization

// Theme Support
- Light/dark mode toggle
- Color tokens in _data/designTokens
- CSS custom properties for theming
- Persistent theme selection

// Design Tokens (src/_data/designTokens/)
- Colors:
  - Base colors defined in colors.json
  - Custom CSS properties:
    - Base Dark: #343434
    - Base Light: #FBFBFB
    - Primary Highlight: #4129D6 (Royal Blue)
    - Secondary Highlight: #D62967 (Deep Pink)
    - Tertiary Highlight: #BED629 (Lime Green)
    - --color-text
    - --color-text-accent
    - --color-bg
    - --color-bg-accent
    - --color-bg-accent-2
    - --color-primary
    - --color-secondary
    - --color-tertiary
- Gradients:
  - --gradient-rainbow
  - --gradient-conic
  - --gradient-stripes

